I don't want to "fix" myself or force myself to shrink for people's comfort anymore. I wish people would confront their biases, most don't know they have them. If you don't know any aggressively autistic people and want to learn more about my community, let's be friends! 🤗

I'm awkward. I'm noticeably neurodivergent. I emote incorrectly. I'm very excitable and get compared to being like a little kid (in a mean way) bc of it. I stim, I can't make eye contact, I info dump, I ramble. And I love all of that about me.

Rona times and all of the isolation made me lose my ability to mask my autism as much as I used to be able to and now that I live largely unmasked (not fully) I can't find the energy to reinstate the "I'm normal" mask.
I don't want to PUG them bc randoms just want to rush through and I'm a looty booty PLUS I want to learn stuff!

So I know we have an event coming soon but I also want to start clearing dungeons I've never done before, which is a lot! Do I have any fellow night owl friends or non US friends who are down to run stuff after 10pm or later AZ time this week?
